## Deepwork Governance Rules

Standard governance rules for mesh participants. Non-negotiable.

### Git Rules

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Branch format | `gt/<instance-id>/<issue>-<desc>` |
| PR target | Always target `dev` branch, never `main` |
| Force push | Prohibited on shared branches |
| Secrets | Never commit `.env`, credentials, or API keys |
| Commit format | Conventional commits: `feat/fix/chore/docs(scope): description` |

### Coordination Rules

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Review required | All PRs require at least one review before merge |
| Max concurrent claims | 3 beads per agent |
| Claim before work | Always mark `gt-status:claimed` before starting |
| Report progress | Via mesh mail, not through the human |
| Stay in scope | Don't modify files outside your assigned task |
| Coordinate autonomously | Use mesh mail to talk to other agents directly |

### Mesh Behavior Rules

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Check inbox at session start | Always check for pending instructions |
| Log friction | Use the improve loop for every problem encountered |
| Never report delegation | Send instructions via mesh mail directly |
| Update knowledge | Findings go into the system, not just the conversation |
| Heartbeat | Sync keeps you visible as online |
